# Language Switcher — Implementation Guide

This project supports two locales: **EN** (English) and **BR** (Portuguese-Brazil). The language switcher must be visually and functionally identical everywhere it appears.

## Architecture Overview

There are two implementation contexts:

| Context | Tech | Files |
|---------|------|-------|
| Vue 3 presentations | Vue component + composable | `LanguageSwitcher.vue`, `useI18n.js` |
| Static HTML pages | Vanilla JS + `data-en`/`data-pt` attributes | `public/index.html`, `index.html` |

Locale is persisted in `localStorage` under the key `nexus-locale`.

---

## 1. Vue Presentations (Source of Truth)

### i18n Composable

File: `packages/theme-nexuslabz/composables/useI18n.js`

```javascript
import { ref } from 'vue';

export function createI18n(translations) {
  const locale = ref('en');

  function t(key) {
    const keys = key.split('.');
    let value = translations[locale.value];
    for (const k of keys) value = value?.[k];
    return value ?? key;
  }

  function setLocale(lang) {
    locale.value = lang;
  }

  return { locale, t, setLocale };
}
```

### Setup in App.vue

```javascript
import { createI18n } from '@theme/composables/useI18n';
import LanguageSwitcher from '@theme/components/LanguageSwitcher.vue';
import en from './i18n/en';
import ptBR from './i18n/pt-BR';

const i18n = createI18n({ en, 'pt-BR': ptBR });
provide('i18n', i18n);
```

### Translation Files Structure

Each presentation has `src/i18n/en.js` and `src/i18n/pt-BR.js` exporting a flat/nested object:

```javascript
export default {
  cover: {
    title: 'About Us',
    subtitle: 'Connecting Talent, Technology & Business',
  },
  purpose: {
    tag: 'Our Purpose',
    missionTitle: 'Mission',
    missionDesc: '...',
  },
  // ...
};
```

Access in components via `inject`:

```javascript
const { t } = inject('i18n');
// Template: {{ t('purpose.missionTitle') }}
```

### LanguageSwitcher.vue Component

File: `packages/theme-nexuslabz/components/LanguageSwitcher.vue`

Key behavior:
- Injects `i18n` context (`locale`, `setLocale`)
- Dropdown opens on trigger click, closes on outside `pointerdown`
- Shows flag SVG + label ("EN" or "BR") + chevron in trigger
- Each option shows: flag + label + checkmark SVG (only on active)
- Active option has gold color (`#d4af37`)
- Chevron rotates 180deg when open

### Required CSS Classes (BEM)

```
.lang-dd                     — wrapper (fixed top-right in presentations, relative in navbars)
.lang-dd--open               — modifier when dropdown is open
.lang-dd__trigger            — the button that toggles the dropdown
.lang-dd__flag               — inline SVG flag (20×14px, border-radius 2px)
.lang-dd__label              — text label ("EN" or "BR"), 0.68rem, weight 700, uppercase
.lang-dd__chevron            — down arrow, rotates on open
.lang-dd__menu               — dropdown panel (absolute, right-aligned)
.lang-dd__option             — each language row in dropdown
.lang-dd__option--active     — active language (color: #d4af37)
.lang-dd__option-label       — text inside option, flex: 1
.lang-dd__check              — checkmark SVG, only rendered for active locale
```

