## 4. Adding a New Language

1. **Vue presentations**: Add entry to `languages` array in `LanguageSwitcher.vue`, create `src/i18n/{locale}.js` file, import in `App.vue` and pass to `createI18n`.
2. **Static pages**: Add a new `<button class="lang-dd__option">` in HTML, add a new flag SVG, extend the `setLocale()` function, and add `data-{locale}` attributes to all translatable elements.
3. **Flag**: Create a simplified inline SVG (same viewBox `0 0 640 480`).
4. **localStorage key**: Remains `nexus-locale`, value is the locale code (e.g. `'es'`).

---

## 5. Checklist for Consistency

When creating or modifying the language switcher on any page:

- [ ] Uses `lang-dd` BEM class naming (NOT `lang-switcher`, `lang-trigger`, etc.)
- [ ] Labels are **"EN"** and **"BR"** (NOT "English", "Português", "Inglês")
- [ ] Active option shows gold checkmark SVG
- [ ] Active option text is gold (`#d4af37`)
- [ ] Chevron rotates 180deg when open
- [ ] Dropdown closes on outside `pointerdown` (NOT `click`)
- [ ] Locale persisted in `localStorage` key `nexus-locale`
- [ ] Flag SVGs are identical across all pages
- [ ] `document.documentElement.lang` is updated on locale change
